---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "April 19, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About HyroxVault | Editorial Team, Review Process & Disclosure"
  description="Who writes HyroxVault, how we test products, our editorial and correction policies, and full affiliate disclosure."
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: "About", url: "/about/" }]}
>
  <section class="container-main py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-4">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black mb-6">
        <span class="text-gradient-accent">About HyroxVault</span>
      </h1>

      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p class="text-xl text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          HyroxVault is an independent, editorially-driven resource for Hyrox athletes.
          We publish race guides, training programs, gear reviews, and supplement
          recommendations based on real training, testing, and competition data — not
          press releases.
        </p>

        <h2>Who runs HyroxVault</h2>
        <p>
          HyroxVault is run by a small editorial team of Hyrox racers, certified strength
          coaches, and sports-nutrition writers based in Europe. We compete in Hyrox events,
          train athletes preparing for them, and read the peer-reviewed research on the
          supplements and gear we recommend. Every article is reviewed by at least one
          editor with lived racing experience before it goes live.
        </p>
        <p>
          Want to know more about a specific contributor or suggest a guest post?
          Use the contact form at the bottom of this page.
        </p>

        <h2>How we pick products</h2>
        <p>
          We cover four product categories: <strong>supplements, running shoes,
          training gear, and race-day accessories</strong>. Our recommendations are
          based on:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Published research</strong> — for supplements, we rely on
            meta-analyses and position statements from organisations such as the ISSN
            and ACSM, not brand marketing.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Third-party certifications</strong> — where relevant we highlight
            products with NSF Certified for Sport or Informed Sport testing.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Community consensus</strong> — what experienced Hyrox age-group and
            Pro division athletes are actually using and what is widely reviewed well.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Value</strong> — we highlight options that offer strong value for a
            typical working athlete, not just the most expensive product.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Where we call something an "Editor's Pick" or "Best Value", that reflects our
          read of the available evidence and public reviews — not a certification, and
          not a promise of outcome for any individual athlete.
        </p>

        <h2>Editorial independence</h2>
        <p>
          We do not accept paid placements, sponsored rankings, or "pay-to-play"
          inclusion in our buying guides. Where a brand relationship exists it is
          disclosed, and it does not determine which products we recommend.
        </p>

        <h2>Affiliate disclosure</h2>
        <p>
          HyroxVault may earn commissions when readers buy through some of our outbound
          links. Depending on your country, these links may point to retailers such as
          Amazon, Gymgrossisten, Myprotein, iHerb, or direct brand stores. Commissions,
          where they apply, are paid by the retailer at no extra cost to you and do not
          influence which products are featured.
        </p>
        <p>
          Affiliate links are marked with <code>rel="nofollow sponsored"</code> and,
          where product cards appear, a small disclosure notice nearby.
        </p>

        <h2>Corrections and fact-checking</h2>
        <p>
          We check every factual claim — race distances, station standards, product
          specs, commission rates, supplement dosages — against primary sources before
          publishing. If you spot an error, let us know via the contact form at the bottom of this page
          and we'll fix it within 48 hours. Material corrections are logged at the bottom
          of the affected article with a date and a one-line description.
        </p>

        <h2>Medical disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          Training and supplementation advice on HyroxVault is general information, not
          personalised medical guidance. Hyrox is a demanding race. If you have an
          underlying health condition, are pregnant, or are taking prescribed medication,
          speak with a qualified healthcare professional before starting a new training
          programme or supplement protocol.
        </p>

        <h2>What we cover</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Racing Guide</strong> — Hyrox format, the 8 stations, categories, pacing, race-week prep.</li>
          <li><strong>Training Plans</strong> — beginner, intermediate, advanced, and doubles programmes with week-by-week structure.</li>
          <li><strong>Gear Reviews</strong> — shoes, clothing, compression, belts, bags, and home-gym equipment.</li>
          <li><strong>Supplements</strong> — creatine, protein, gels, pre-workout, electrolytes, recovery stacks.</li>
          <li><strong>Competitions</strong> — upcoming races, sign-up links, and city guides.</li>
          <li><strong>Blog</strong> — race recaps, training tips, deep-dives on technique and strategy.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Relationship with Hyrox</h2>
        <p>
          HyroxVault is an independent publication and is not affiliated with, endorsed
          by, or officially connected to Hyrox GmbH. "Hyrox" and related marks are
          trademarks of their respective owners and are used here only to identify the
          sport and its events.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For general enquiries, editorial pitches, or corrections, please use the contact
          form on this page. We aim to respond within 48 hours.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "HyroxVault",
    "url": "https://hyroxvault.com",
    "logo": "https://hyroxvault.com/og-default.png",
    "description": "Independent editorial site covering Hyrox racing, training, gear and supplements.",
    "foundingDate": "2026",
    "sameAs": [],
    "publishingPrinciples": "https://hyroxvault.com/about/",
    "ethicsPolicy": "https://hyroxvault.com/about/",
    "diversityPolicy": "https://hyroxvault.com/about/"
  })} />
</BaseLayout>
